   "source": [
    "# SHAP Generation and Explanations\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to generate SHAP explanations for compound selectivity models in this repository.\n",
    "\n",
    "It includes:\n",
    "- Optional end-to-end training (dataset -> features -> split -> model)\n",
    "- SHAP generation from an existing split/model pair\n",
    "- Atom-level SHAP visualizations on molecules\n",
    "- SHAP explanations for custom SMILES strings"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "137ba1e0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Workflow Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Configure paths and model settings.\n",
    "2. Either train a new model or reuse existing split/model artifacts.\n",
    "3. Compute SHAP values for a selected split.\n",
    "4. Render atom-level SHAP heatmaps for selected compounds.\n",
    "5. Explain one custom SMILES and render its SHAP map."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
